1 pound Baby Carrots
2.25 ounce Mike’s Hot Honey®
3.5 ounce Garlic Herb Butter
1 teaspoon Cooking Oil
Salt
Pepper

Set aside 2 TBSP garlic herb butter to soften to room temperature.

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees.

Toss carrots on a baking sheet with a drizzle of oil, salt, and pepper.

Roast carrots on top rack 18-22 minutes, or until softened.

Remove baking sheet from oven. Toss carrots with softened garlic herb butter and hot honey to taste.

**Recipe Suggestion (Additional ingredients not included.)**: Chop equal parts chives and parsley. Toss your sweet-and-savory glazed carrots with the herbs, softened garlic herb butter, and hot honey to taste.